//Normal Object Copy (=)
// Observation
// No new object is created.
// Both variables point to the same memory location.
// Changes in one object affect the other object.
 
// Shallow Copy Using Spread Operator
// Observation
// Creates a new outer object.
// Nested objects are shared by reference.
// Changes to top-level properties do not affect the original object.
// Changes to nested properties affect both objects.

// Shallow Copy Using Object.assign()
// Observation
// Creates a new object.
// Copies only first-level properties.
// Nested objects remain shared.

//Deep Copy Using JSON Methods
// Observation
// Creates a completely independent copy.
// Nested objects are copied separately.
// Changes in the copied object do not affect the original object.

// Deep Copy Using structuredClone
// Observation
// Creates a true deep copy.
// Copies nested objects and arrays completely.
// Original and copied objects are fully independent.

Conclusion
// Normal Copy shares the same object reference.
// Shallow Copy creates a new outer object but shares nested object references.
// Deep Copy creates a fully independent object, including all nested objects and arrays.